Constructor Detail

DisplayItemGroup

public DisplayItemGroup()
Creates a new display items "invisible" group with no label. The "invisible" means that the group (OPTGROUP) won't be rendered, but its child-options (OPTION) will be rendered.

See Also:
SelectGroup.isNoGroup(), SelectGroup.NO_GROUP

DisplayItemGroup

public DisplayItemGroup(String label)
Creates a new display items group with given label and with no child-options.

Parameters:
label - The label for this group.
See Also:
SelectGroup.isNoGroup(), SelectGroup.NO_GROUP

DisplayItemGroup

public DisplayItemGroup(String label,
                        List<DisplayItem> options)
Creates a new display items group with given label and with given child-options.

Parameters:
label - The label for this group.
options - The options that this group will contain, must not be null.
See Also:
SelectGroup.isNoGroup(), SelectGroup.NO_GROUP
Method Detail

isEnabledEmpty

public boolean isEnabledEmpty()
Provides whether the group contains enabled items.

Returns:
A Boolean that is true when the group contains no enabled child option.

getEnabledOptions

public List<DisplayItem> getEnabledOptions()
Provides enabled only child options. The returned list is modifiable but it cannot be used to alter the disabled status of options.

Returns:
The list of enabled child options.
